<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_cd7bdc03-9330-42cc-8866-504c0c39fd32" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>H4F1</sptc><title id="_28b21d22-9796-4948-9a6f-12fedadcf4f1">Wet areas</title><archive-num>2019: F2.4.1</archive-num><subclause id="_713c9a5c-cd55-4122-b955-1cb17a87bcf0" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_75fcb429-fa0a-4ec0-b7b8-5fb3174c3b30">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A building is to be constructed to avoid the likelihood of—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_39e849dc-0e57-4fd0-bf9c-c671409b78dd">the creation of any unhealthy or dangerous conditions; or</li><li id="_29bc25c4-91dc-4eee-9f81-e23d96e1e9c4">damage to building elements,</li></ol><p>caused by dampness or water overflow from bathrooms, laundries and the like.</p></subclause></clause>